<DOC><DOCNO> AP881223-0234 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-23-88 1519EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-FortuneFinancial     12-23 0196</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Fortune Financial,0206</SECOND><HEAD>Baldwin Securities Unit Makes Offer For Fortune Financial</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Baldwin Securities Corp. said Friday it offeredto buy Fortune Financial Group Inc., a Florida savings and loanholding company, for about $180 million.   The $33-a-share offer by the New York investment firm includes$27 in cash and $6 in senior preferred stock. It is conditioned uponacceptance by Fortune's board of directors.   The Baldwin offer is the third Fortune Financial has receivedfrom a company or person with close ties to Singer Co., the defensecontractor that financier Paul A. Bilzerian took private about ayear ago.   A federal grand jury indicted Bilzerian on fraud chargesWednesday in connection with four unsuccessful takeover attempts,none of which involved Fortune Financial.   Baldwin Chairman Arthur G. Cohenis is a Singer director. Offersfor Fortune have been made in the past few months _ and laterwithdrawn _ from Bilzerian, Singer's chairman, and Alex Spanos,another Singer director.   Also vying for the Clearwater, Fla.-based Fortune Financial isthe New York investment firm Dyson-Kissner-Moran Corp., which onWednesday disclosed a $170 million offer, which includes $27 in cashand $4 in preferred stock.</TEXT></DOC>